# Non-secret: these are PUBLIC keys, safe to commit. This file lets
# `git log --show-signature` verify locally without contacting GitHub. home.nix
# materialises it at ~/.config/git/allowed_signers.
#
# Format (one signer per line):  <principal> <keytype> <base64-key> [comment]
#
# ROTATING: add the new key on its own line — never replace or remove one. SSH
# signing keys carry no validity window, so dropping a line reverts every commit it
# ever signed to "unverified". Same rule applies to the public half on GitHub: it
# stays uploaded forever. See docs/hardware-acceptance.md, "Commit signing".
